Record Class Path

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
io.github.kaktushose.proteus.graph.Path
Record Components:
edges - a List of all previous Edges
head - the Type that is currently the result of this path. In other words, this is the Type that the last Edge in the list of edges maps to and thus the Type that the next Edge has to start with.
@Internal public record Path(@NotNull List<Edge> edges, @NotNull Type<Object> head) extends Record
Representation of an unfinished path.

  • Method Details

    • addEdge

      public Path addEdge(@NotNull @NotNull Type<?> intermediate, @Nullable Graph.Vertex vertex)
      Adds a new edge to this path. This will create a copy of this path, the underlying list of edges of this path will not be modified.
      Parameters:
      intermediate - the Type that this edge maps into. Will become the new head
      vertex - the Mapper.UniMapper that maps from the head of this path to the given intermediate Type. Can be null, if head and intermediate share the same Format.
      Returns:
      a copy of this path with the given edge added to it
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the vertex is null and head and intermediate don't share the same Format
      UnsupportedOperationException - if the vertex is null and head and intermediate don't have a format (Format.None)

      Returns:
      a copy of this path with the updated head
